2500|$|Making {{statistic}} {{and skill}} checks in GURPS is {{the reverse of}} the mechanics of most other RPGs, where the higher the total of the <b>die</b> <b>roll,</b> the better. GURPS players hope to roll {{as low as possible}} under the tested statistic's rating or skill's level. If the roll is {{less than or equal to}} that number, the check succeeds. There is no [...] "target number" [...] or [...] "difficulty rating" [...] set by the Game Master, as would be the case in many other RPG systems. Instead the GM will apply various modifiers to add or subtract to the skill level. In this way, positive modifiers increase the chance for success by adding to the stat or skill level you must roll under while negative modifiers deduct from it, making things more difficult.|$|E
